WEBVTT

00:00.960 --> 00:01.858
- I'M DOING THE RIGHT THING.

00:01.890 --> 00:03.448
RIGHT, ADAM, MOVING HOME?

00:03.480 --> 00:04.959
- LOOK, SARAH,
YOU'RE DOING THE RIGHT THING.

00:05.000 --> 00:06.615
- I TOLD YOU WE DON'T HAVE
A CHOICE.

00:06.660 --> 00:07.922
I'M OUT OF MONEY.

00:07.970 --> 00:08.891
- I WANT DADDY.

00:08.930 --> 00:11.387
- SHE OPENLY PREFERS JOEL,
AND IT IS FINE.

00:11.420 --> 00:12.557
- SO YOU'RE SAYING
THAT YOU'LL HAVE A BABY

00:12.590 --> 00:13.909
WITH ME IN THREE YEARS?

00:13.940 --> 00:15.100
- YEAH.
WHO'S THIS?

00:15.150 --> 00:17.869
- THAT'S JABBAR.
HE WANTED TO MEET HIS DAD.

00:17.910 --> 00:19.218
- THEY WEREN'T
OFFICIALLY BOOKED,

00:19.260 --> 00:20.636
SO IT'S NOT GONNA GO
IN THEIR RECORDS.

00:20.670 --> 00:22.353
- IT WASN'T MY WEED.

00:22.400 --> 00:24.800
- SHE THINKS THAT
HE MAY HAVE ASPERGER'S.

00:24.850 --> 00:25.805
- KRISTINA,
I'VE SEEN AUTISTIC KIDS.

00:25.850 --> 00:27.397
THE LESSINGS' KID WITH
THE HAND FLAPPING--

00:27.440 --> 00:28.532
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG
WITH MY SON.

00:28.580 --> 00:32.983
- TO DREW, AND AMBER,
AND MY SHINING ANGEL, SARAH.

00:33.030 --> 00:34.474
WELCOME HOME.
- WELCOME HOME.

00:34.510 --> 00:36.125
- WELCOME HOME.
- HEAR. HEAR.

00:37.200 --> 00:41.375
[soft thuds]

00:44.590 --> 00:45.966
[animal chirps]

00:46.010 --> 00:47.318
- HE'S BACK.

00:47.350 --> 00:49.659
[Talking Heads'
Once In A Lifetime]

00:51.560 --> 00:55.803
- AND YOU MAY FIND YOURSELF
LIVING IN A SHOTGUN SHACK

00:55.840 --> 01:00.083
AND YOU MAY FIND YOURSELF
IN ANOTHER PART OF THE WORLD

01:00.120 --> 01:02.702
AND YOU MAY FIND YOURSELF
BEHIND THE WHEEL

01:02.750 --> 01:05.366
OF A LARGE AUTOMOBILE
[creaking]

01:05.410 --> 01:09.232
AND YOU MAY FIND YOURSELF
IN A BEAUTIFUL HOUSE

01:09.270 --> 01:10.953
WITH A BEAUTIFUL WIFE

01:11.000 --> 01:15.892
AND YOU MAY ASK YOURSELF,
"WELL, HOW DID I GET HERE?"

01:15.930 --> 01:19.138
LE'I'I'ING Tl-iE DAYS GO BY
[hisses]

01:19.180 --> 01:21.694
- AAAH! GAH!
- LE'I'I'ING THE DAYS GO BY

01:21.730 --> 01:23.698
WATER FLOWING _UNDERGROUND
[chirping]

01:23.730 --> 01:26.073
INTO THE BLUE AGAIN

01:26.120 --> 01:28.179
AFTER THE MONEY'S GONE

01:28.220 --> 01:29.767
ONCE IN A LIFETIME

01:29.810 --> 01:31.949
[opossum hisses]

01:31.980 --> 01:34.801
- SO YOUR MOM SAID YOU WANTED
TO KNOW ABOUT YOUR OLD MAN.

01:37.610 --> 01:38.918
YOU KNOW WHAT,
LET'S START WITH YOU.

01:38.960 --> 01:41.292
ARE YOU MARRIED?
- NO.

01:41.340 --> 01:43.956
- HMM. OKAY.
YOU SEEING ANYONE?

01:44.000 --> 01:47.026
- MM. MM-MMM.
- HMM. KEEPING IT LOOSE.

01:47.070 --> 01:48.094
I GOT YOU.

01:48.140 --> 01:49.346
YOU KNOW,
IF YOU'RE HAVING TROUBLE

01:49.380 --> 01:51.416
MEETING LADIES,
IT COULD BE YOUR CAR.

01:51.450 --> 01:54.726
WHAT KIND OF CAR DO YOU DRIVE?
- I DON'T HAVE A CAR.

01:54.760 --> 01:57.695
- YOU DON'T--HMM.
YOU HAVE YOUR LICENSE, RIGHT?

01:57.730 --> 02:02.872
- LICENSE?
- UM...

02:02.910 --> 02:06.289
THOSE WERE MY THREE KID JOKES.
I'M ALL OUT OF MATERIAL.

02:06.330 --> 02:10.369
WELL, UM...
OH, THERE'S MOM.

02:10.400 --> 02:14.769
HI, MOM.
IT'S GOING GREAT.

02:14.820 --> 02:18.927
THIS IS FUN THOUGH.
YOU LIKE PANCAKES?

02:18.960 --> 02:22.270
- NO.
I LIKE WAFFLES BE'I'I'ER.

02:22.310 --> 02:24.278
- OKAY, LET'S MOVE IT, PEOPLE.
COME ON.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.062
I HAVE A MEETING.
PLEASE.

02:26.110 --> 02:27.338
- DAD SAID
HE COULD'VE TOOKEN ME.

02:27.380 --> 02:31.339
- OH, SWEETIE, I WANT
TO DRIVE YOU, ALL RIGHT?

02:31.390 --> 02:34.314
WE'RE BONDING.
WHAT THE FU--!

02:34.360 --> 02:37.045
- MOM!
- FUDGE! FUDGE, SWEETIE.

02:37.080 --> 02:39.321
OH, MY GOSH.
- COME ON, SWEETHEART.

02:39.360 --> 02:42.841
- OH, YEAH. PLEASE.
BY ALL MEANS TAKE YOUR TIME.

02:42.880 --> 02:46.748
GO FOR IT. I ONLY HAVE A MEETING
WITH A SUPREME COURT JUDGE SO...

02:46.780 --> 02:48.190
OH, YEAH, SURE.

02:48.230 --> 02:51.882
YEAH, MAKE SURE
SHE HAS HER LUNCHBOX. GREAT.

02:51.930 --> 02:54.194
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

02:54.240 --> 02:55.684
NO.
- MOMMY.

02:55.720 --> 02:57.711
- NO.
- WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

02:57.760 --> 02:59.546
- SWEETIE, YOU CAN LEARN
FROM THIS.

02:59.590 --> 03:02.036
THIS IS A BAD PERSON.
- [sighs]

03:03.070 --> 03:05.004
AND WHEN SOMEONE DOESN'T FOLLOW
THOSE LAWS,

03:05.040 --> 03:08.737
SOCIETY BREAKS DOWN.

03:08.770 --> 03:11.113
[honks horn]

03:11.150 --> 03:12.526
[laughs]

03:22.230 --> 03:25.745
- THIS IS SO GREAT.
SO SPECIAL.

03:25.790 --> 03:29.476
IT'S YOUR FIRST DAY...
IN THE NEW PLACE.

03:29.510 --> 03:33.469
AND IT'S JUST...
GONNA BE...

03:33.520 --> 03:36.990
ALL BRAND-NEW
AND DIFFERENT THAN THE...

03:37.040 --> 03:38.029
- MOM...
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:38.070 --> 03:39.890
- I DON'T KNOW.
IT WAS SOMETHING I WAS TRYING.

03:39.940 --> 03:40.861
NO?
- MM-MMM.

03:40.910 --> 03:44.619
- ALL RIGHT. GOOD-BYE.
I LOVE YOU. OKAY.

03:44.670 --> 03:48.288
YOU CAN BE THE BEST!
I BELIEVE IN YOU.

03:48.330 --> 03:49.979
JUST BE YOU!

03:53.880 --> 03:56.155
- MM-MMM

03:58.650 --> 04:01.505
WHEN WE WERE YOUNG,
WE WERE SMALL

04:01.550 --> 04:04.678
BUT WE DIDN'T KNOW IT

04:04.720 --> 04:08.235
AHH AHH AHH

04:09.210 --> 04:11.861
WHEN YOU WERE HURT,
YOU WOULD SMILE

04:11.900 --> 04:15.074
SO YOU DIDN'T
SHOW IT

04:15.110 --> 04:18.284
AHH AHH AHH

04:19.290 --> 04:25.354
AND I-I-I-I CAN'T
BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

04:30.130 --> 04:33.338
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

04:35.240 --> 04:37.856
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

04:40.900 --> 04:41.855
- LET'S GO. LET'S HIT IT.

04:41.900 --> 04:44.039
HEY, DID YOU BRUSH YOUR TEETH?
- HEY, MAX.

04:44.070 --> 04:45.719
- THINK HE DID.
- MAX.

04:45.760 --> 04:48.035
MAX, WE HAD A DEAL, REMEMBER?
- OKAY. OKAY.

04:48.080 --> 04:50.935
- REGULAR CLOTHES TO SCHOOL,
BUT THE PIRATE COSTUME AT HOME.

04:50.980 --> 04:52.288
- I CHANGED MY MIND.
- WELL, I DIDN'T, OKAY?

04:52.320 --> 04:53.901
SO I WANT YOU BACK INSI--
- MOM SAID.

04:53.940 --> 04:55.259
- HONEY, I'M SORRY.

04:55.290 --> 04:56.518
- "MOM SAID."
- WE DON'T HAVE TIME TO CHANGE.

04:56.570 --> 04:58.014
OKAY? I'M--HE WAS SAD.

04:58.050 --> 04:59.779
- WELL, HE CAN'T KEEP GOING
TO SCHOOL LIKE THAT, OKAY?

04:59.810 --> 05:01.152
KIDS ARE GOING TO THINK
HE'S A FREAK.

05:01.190 --> 05:02.259
HOW'S HE GONNA MAKE
ANY FRIENDS?

05:02.300 --> 05:03.813
NOW, I KNEW KIDS THAT LIKE
WHEN I WAS AT SCHOOL.

05:03.850 --> 05:05.124
ONCE YOU'RE A FREAK,
YOU'RE ALWAYS A FREAK.

05:05.160 --> 05:06.434
- I GET IT.
BELIEVE ME. I KNOW.

05:06.470 --> 05:08.222
I DEAL WITH THIS
EVERY SINGLE DAY, OKAY?

05:08.270 --> 05:09.851
I'VE TRIED BRIBING HIM,
PLEADING WITH HIM,

05:09.890 --> 05:11.505
THE BUGS, BUYING HIM BUGS,
AND COOKIES AND FOOD.

05:11.550 --> 05:12.926
- I'M SORRY.
- OKAY.

05:12.960 --> 05:14.518
- OKAY? I JUST WANT
TO GET HIM OUT OF THAT THING.

05:14.550 --> 05:16.279
THAT'S ALL.
- I DO TOO.

05:16.310 --> 05:17.891
- ALL RIGHT. I LOVE YOU.
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

05:17.930 --> 05:20.205
OH, WAIT, HONEY,
YOU KNOW, MAYBE THE LESSINGS--

05:20.250 --> 05:21.103
THEY'LL HAVE SOME IDEAS.

05:21.140 --> 05:22.550
- OH, GOD. THE LESSINGS?
IS THAT TONIGHT?

05:22.590 --> 05:23.830
- YEAH, IT'S TONIGHT.
I TOLD YOU YESTERDAY.

05:23.870 --> 05:26.247
THEY'RE REALLY GOOD PEOPLE.
THEY HAVE A SON WITH ASPERGER'S.

05:26.290 --> 05:28.246
- WELL, IT'S NOT DINNER, IS IT?
- NO.

05:28.290 --> 05:29.245
- REMEMBER THAT TIME
WE WENT OVER THERE

05:29.290 --> 05:30.427
AND THEY MADE DINNER?
- YEAH.

05:30.460 --> 05:32.109
- THEY DIDN'T PREHEAT THE OVEN
UNTIL WE'D BEEN THERE

05:32.150 --> 05:33.902
FOR THREE AND A HALF HOURS--
IT WAS UNCONSCIONABLE.

05:33.950 --> 05:35.087
I FELT LIKE I WAS BEING
HELD CAPTIVE.

05:35.120 --> 05:36.360
I CAN'T GO THROUGH THAT AGAIN.
- HONEY, SAY GOOD-BYE.

05:36.400 --> 05:38.436
- GOOD-BYE.
- TO YOUR SON.

05:38.470 --> 05:41.576
- I KNOW. GOOD-BYE, BUDDY.
I LOVE YOU.

05:41.610 --> 05:43.498
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH, BABE.
SEE YOU.

05:43.550 --> 05:44.778
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

05:44.820 --> 05:46.617
- HEY, YOU KNOW, WE DON'T
EVEN KNOW FOR SURE

05:46.650 --> 05:47.958
THAT HE HAS ASPERGER'S.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.275
- I KNOW.
- HE'S NOT THE LESSING KID.

05:50.310 --> 05:52.062
- I KNOW.

05:58.080 --> 06:00.241
- THAT WAS TERRIFIC.

06:00.290 --> 06:04.454
- [clears throat]
SO. ..

06:04.500 --> 06:05.592
IT'S BEEN A WHILE, CROSBY.

06:05.640 --> 06:09.280
- YEAH. LIKE, UH, FIVE YEARS
AND NINE MONTHS A WHILE.

06:09.330 --> 06:11.537
- I GUESS.

06:11.570 --> 06:15.506
- HEY, I-I HATE TO ASK YOU THIS,
BUT, UM, YOU'RE SURE

06:15.540 --> 06:18.168
THAT HE'S MINE, YEAH?

06:18.200 --> 06:21.442
- YEAH.
I'M--I'M PRE'ITY SURE.

06:21.480 --> 06:23.994
- YOU DIDN'T HAVE, LIKE,
RELATIONS WITH ANYONE ELSE

06:24.030 --> 06:25.065
DURING THAT SAME PERIOD?

06:25.100 --> 06:27.034
- HE'S YOURS.
- OKAY.

06:27.070 --> 06:28.719
WELL, HEY, IF YOU GUYS
ARE IN TOWN AGAIN,

06:28.760 --> 06:30.443
YOU KNOW,
WE SHOULD DO THIS AGAIN.

06:30.490 --> 06:31.969
- WELL, UM...
[clears throat]

06:32.010 --> 06:35.218
ACTUALLY, WE MOVED BACK.

06:35.250 --> 06:36.899
- YOU--REALLY?
- YEAH.

06:36.940 --> 06:38.350
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

06:38.390 --> 06:39.357
- 'CAUSE IN YOUR EMAIL,

06:39.390 --> 06:42.279
YOU SAID THAT YOU WERE
JUST COMING TO TOWN,

06:42.330 --> 06:44.946
NOT THAT YOU HAD
MOVED BACK...

06:44.990 --> 06:48.084
WITH MY KID.

06:48.130 --> 06:51.156
- MAYBE YOU DON'T REMEMBER
THAT I CALLED YOU...

06:51.200 --> 06:54.749
MANY TIMES.

06:55.790 --> 06:58.509
CROSBY, JABBAR IS STARTING
TO GET TO THAT AGE

06:58.550 --> 07:00.518
WHERE HE'S ASKING
ABOUT HIS DAD.

07:00.550 --> 07:01.994
I WOULD LOVE IT

07:02.040 --> 07:05.692
IF THE TWO OF YOU DEVELOPED
A RELATIONSHIP.

07:07.700 --> 07:10.146
- OKAY. YEAH.
- YEAH?

07:10.180 --> 07:11.351
- YEAH. ABSOLUTELY.

07:11.390 --> 07:13.119
- MAYBE YOU GUYS
CAN GET TOGETHER

07:13.150 --> 07:14.287
AN AFTERNOON THIS WEEKEND.

07:14.330 --> 07:15.149
- THIS WEEKEND.
- YEAH.

07:15.190 --> 07:16.805
- THE ONE COMING UP
THIS WEEKEND?

07:16.850 --> 07:20.149
- YEAH, THAT ONE.
- YEAH. UM...

07:20.190 --> 07:21.327
MAN, THAT SOUNDS REALLY GOOD.

07:21.370 --> 07:24.919
BUT, UM, I'M ACTUALLY
GOING OUT OF TOWN THIS WEEKEND.

07:24.960 --> 07:26.712
- OH.

07:39.660 --> 07:42.481
- WHAT?
- NOTHING.

07:47.010 --> 07:48.420
HMM.
- DAD!

07:48.460 --> 07:49.666
- WELL, HONEY, I MEAN,

07:49.710 --> 07:51.325
YOU DIDN'T MOVE ALL THE WAY
BACK TO BERKELEY

07:51.360 --> 07:52.975
TO SERVE UP A BUNCH
OF WHISKEY SOURS

07:53.020 --> 07:54.089
TO ALCOHOLICS.

07:54.120 --> 07:56.224
YOU SHOULD BE ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THAT EQUATION.

07:56.260 --> 07:58.467
- OKAY. I SHOULD--
I SHOULD BE AN ALCOHOLIC?

07:58.510 --> 07:59.499
- NO.
- NO.

07:59.540 --> 08:02.714
- YOU SHOULD BE AN EXECUTIVE.
- COME ON, ZEEK.

08:02.750 --> 08:06.231
LEAVE HER ALONE.
SHE LOVES BARTENDING.

08:06.270 --> 08:08.784
RIGHT, SWEETIE?
- YES, MOTHER, IT COMPLETES ME.

08:08.830 --> 08:11.060
- WELL, NEVER MIND.
YOU RAISED TWO KIDS ON IT.

08:11.110 --> 08:12.486
IT'S A GOOD LIVING.

08:12.520 --> 08:14.966
- YOU SHOULD BE
IN ADVERTISING AND PR.

08:15.010 --> 08:15.897
I MEAN, COME ON.

08:15.940 --> 08:17.316
YOU DID ALL OF THE MARKETING
AND DESIGN

08:17.350 --> 08:19.625
FOR YOUR EX-HUSBAND'S BAND.

08:19.670 --> 08:21.422
IF HE HADN'T THROWN
HIS CAREER IN THE TOILET--

08:21.460 --> 08:23.348
- ZEEK, COME ON.
LEAVE HER ALONE.

08:23.390 --> 08:25.278
SARAH KNOWS
WHAT SHE'S CAPABLE OF.

08:25.330 --> 08:29.221
- WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?
- UM, THAT YOU KNOW YOURSELF.

08:29.260 --> 08:31.774
- AND MY LIMITS?
- I MEANT IT IN A GOOD WAY.

08:31.820 --> 08:33.264
- LET ME TELL THE TWO OF YOU
SOMETHING.

08:33.300 --> 08:35.507
IT'S NOT TOO LATE TO LEARN
SOME PARENTING SKILLS, OKAY?

08:35.540 --> 08:36.780
BOTH OF YOU.
- [laughs]

08:36.820 --> 08:38.128
- YOU CAN TAKE A CLASS
OR READ A BOOK.

08:38.170 --> 08:39.922
- WELL, HERE'S SOME--
NO, THIS IS A GOOD ONE.

08:39.960 --> 08:43.088
ASSISTANT TO CREATIVE EXECUTIVE
AT PANTHEON DESIGN.

08:43.140 --> 08:46.029
SOMEONE UNDERSTANDS
THE AD INDUSTRY. SELF-STARTER.

08:46.070 --> 08:48.209
I MEAN, THAT HAS GOT
SARAH BRAVERMAN

08:48.250 --> 08:49.387
WRITTEN ALL OVER IT.

08:49.420 --> 08:50.387
GET ON THAT.

08:50.420 --> 08:52.103
- DAD, I'M PRETTY SURE
THEY'RE NOT LOOKING

08:52.150 --> 08:54.004
FOR A 38-YEAR-OLD SINGLE MOM
WHO'S BEEN A BARTENDER

08:54.050 --> 08:55.176
FOR 10 YEARS.

08:55.220 --> 08:57.211
- THEY'RE LOOKING
FOR A BRILLIANT DESIGNER CHEAP.

08:57.260 --> 08:58.488
THAT'S YOU.

08:58.530 --> 09:00.157
- I CAN'T DO ANYTHING
WITH YOU STANDING THERE.

09:00.190 --> 09:01.703
- WHY NOT?
- BECAUSE YOU'RE HOVERING.

09:01.740 --> 09:04.152
- I'M NOT HOVERING.
- YEAH. YOU--YOU HOVER.

09:04.190 --> 09:05.987
- I DON'T HOVER.
THIS IS NOT HOVERING.

09:06.020 --> 09:08.329
I'M WAY OVER--
THIS IS HOVERING, LIKE THIS.

09:08.370 --> 09:09.849
[whispers]
GET GOING NOW.

09:24.840 --> 09:27.035
- I DIDN'T EVEN SEE THIS.
- 'SCUSE ME.

09:27.080 --> 09:31.073
[indistinct chatter]

09:33.910 --> 09:38.529
- HEY. ARE YOU NEW?
- UM, YEAH.

09:38.570 --> 09:42.711
I JUST MOVED TO TOWN.
- AMBER HOLT?

09:42.750 --> 09:45.856
- YEAH.
- I'M PRINCIPAL GOMEZ.

09:45.890 --> 09:47.539
- UM...

09:47.580 --> 09:51.027
- CAN WE STEP OUTSIDE
FOR A SECOND?

09:58.450 --> 09:59.553
WE'VE REVIEWED
YOUR TRANSFER FILES

09:59.590 --> 10:01.148
FROM YOUR PREVIOUS SCHOOL
IN FRESNO,

10:01.180 --> 10:02.761
WHICH INDICATE YOU DON'T HAVE
ENOUGH CREDITS

10:02.800 --> 10:04.427
TO QUALIFY AS A JUNIOR.

10:04.460 --> 10:05.529
- WHAT?

10:05.570 --> 10:07.014
- WE THINK YOU'LL BE
MORE SUCCESSFUL

10:07.050 --> 10:08.779
STARTING HERE AT ROOSEVELT
AS A SOPHOMORE.

10:08.810 --> 10:11.699
- YOU'RE--
YOU'RE HOLDING ME BACK?

10:11.740 --> 10:13.321
- WELL, I WOULDN'T LOOK AT IT
LIKE THAT.

10:13.370 --> 10:16.464
- NO. NO. I'M SORRY.
THERE'S--THERE'S NO WAY.

10:16.510 --> 10:17.499
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

10:17.540 --> 10:20.748
I'M NOT GONNA SPEND ANOTHER YEAR
OF MY LIFE HERE.

10:20.790 --> 10:23.406
I CAN'T BE OLDER
THAN EVERYBODY ELSE.

10:23.450 --> 10:26.271
LOOK, PLEASE. PLEASE JUST--
JUST GIVE ME A CHANCE.

10:26.310 --> 10:27.516
- I'M REALLY SORRY, AMBER.

10:27.550 --> 10:31.793
THERE'S REALLY NO OTHER
CHOICE HERE.

11:03.730 --> 11:06.585
- HEY, SON.
- DAD.

11:06.630 --> 11:09.246
- BAD TIME?
- NEVER.

11:09.280 --> 11:13.899
- GREAT. SO HOW'S THE BIG
RE-ORG COMING?

11:13.940 --> 11:15.908
- WELL, DAD, THEY DON'T
CALL IT A RE-ORG.

11:15.950 --> 11:17.258
TH E COM PANY'S EXPAN DING.

11:17.290 --> 11:19.019
WHAT DO YOU NEED?
DO YOU NEED SOME NEW SNEAKERS?

11:19.050 --> 11:20.608
- NO. I JUST CAME HERE
TO VISIT MY SON

11:20.640 --> 11:22.949
FOR NO OTHER REASON
THAN TO VISIT MY SON.

11:22.990 --> 11:24.366
YOU GOT THESE IN A 12?

11:24.400 --> 11:25.640
- I WILL CALL THE WAREHOUSE.

11:25.680 --> 11:28.569
- YOU REMEMBER, UH, THE WORK
THAT, UH, YOUR SISTER SARAH DID

11:28.610 --> 11:30.089
FOR HER EX-HUSBAND SETH'S
ROCK BAND?

11:30.130 --> 11:32.166
MAN, I HATED THAT GUY.
DID YOU LIKE HIM?

11:32.200 --> 11:33.576
- WELL, THAT--
THAT WAS A WHILE AGO.

11:33.620 --> 11:35.099
- WELL, SHE DID
ALL THE CD COVERS, ADAM.

11:35.140 --> 11:36.892
ALL THE POSTERS
FOR THE CONCERTS.

11:36.930 --> 11:39.490
REMEMBER THE ONE SHE DID
WITH THE DOVES AND THE STARS?

11:39.520 --> 11:40.964
THAT WAS DYNAMITE.
- YEAH. YEAH.

11:41.010 --> 11:42.898
- BETTER THAN GOOD.
- UH-HUH.

11:42.940 --> 11:46.410
- ANYWAY, SHE AND I
WERE ON THIS, UH,

11:46.460 --> 11:47.552
CHUCK'S LIST THE OTHER DAY.

11:47.600 --> 11:48.521
- CRAIGSLIST.
- YEAH.

11:48.560 --> 11:49.834
SO WE SAW THIS THING

11:49.880 --> 11:52.428
ON A PANTHEON DESIGN
WEBSITE THINGY.

11:52.470 --> 11:56.258
AND I REMEMBERED THAT THEY DID
SOME WORK FOR YOU ONCE, RIGHT?

11:56.300 --> 11:57.676
- UH-HUH.
- YEAH.

11:57.710 --> 11:58.677
THE FELLA'S NAME
IS EDWIN CHUNG.

11:58.710 --> 12:00.086
YOU KNOW HIM?
- NO.

12:00.130 --> 12:02.098
- I RECKON HE'S A CHINESE FELLA.
- I DON'T KNOW HIM.

12:02.130 --> 12:04.473
- WHAT WOULD BE GREAT
IS IF YOU'D CALL HIM

12:04.510 --> 12:06.501
ON YOUR SISTER'S BEHALF--
YOUR NEW FRIEND EDWIN--

12:06.550 --> 12:07.335
AND, YOU KNOW...

12:07.380 --> 12:08.642
- DAD,
PANTHEON IS A HUGE HOUSE.

12:08.690 --> 12:10.169
PEOPLE ARE DYING
TO WORK THERE.

12:10.210 --> 12:12.235
LOOK, SARAH'S BEEN WORKING
IN A BAR THE LAST 15 YEARS.

12:12.280 --> 12:14.589
- COME ON, ADAM.
SHE'S YOUR SISTER.

12:14.630 --> 12:16.484
I MEAN, CALL, HUH?
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

12:16.520 --> 12:19.592
- OKAY. ALL RIGHT.
I'LL CALL HIM.

12:19.630 --> 12:22.736
- GOOD.
- ANYTHING ELSE?

12:22.770 --> 12:24.692
- HOW'S MY GRANDSON DOING?
WHAT'S THE PLAN?

12:24.740 --> 12:26.662
- I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T KNOW.

12:26.710 --> 12:31.363
- BUT, SONNY,
YOU GOT TO HAVE A PLAN, KID.

12:31.400 --> 12:32.469
YOU CAN DO IT.
- YEAH.

12:32.510 --> 12:34.774
- IT'S JUST A PLAN.
HEY, LET'S GET SOME SHOES.

12:34.820 --> 12:36.026
- LET'S GET SOME SHOES.

12:39.550 --> 12:42.337
- HEY, JOEL, DID YOU,
UM, PREHEAT THE OVEN?

12:42.380 --> 12:45.133
'CAUSE WE HAVE TO MAKE COOKIES
FOR THE FUNDRAISER.

12:45.170 --> 12:49.038
SYDNEY?

12:49.070 --> 12:52.073
HELLO.
- WHY, YOU MUST BE JULIA.

12:52.110 --> 12:54.556
- YOU'RE HERE!
- I LIVE HERE.

12:54.600 --> 12:55.487
- THIS IS RACQUEL.
- HI.

12:55.530 --> 12:56.519
- HI.

12:56.560 --> 12:58.289
- RACQUEL IS CO-CHAIRING
THE FUNDRAISER WITH ME.

12:58.320 --> 13:00.948
WE'RE, UH, WE'RE, UH, WRAPPING
AND WE'RE BAKING.

13:00.980 --> 13:02.493
- YEAH, WELL, THE SCHOOL
NEEDS MONEY.

13:02.540 --> 13:04.496
AND YOU KNOW WHAT GETS HIT FIRST
IS THE ARTS.

13:04.540 --> 13:06.747
I MEAN, YOU KNOW THAT THE FOURTH
AND FIFTH GRADE ORCHESTRA

13:06.780 --> 13:08.668
PROGRAM IS JUST THE TIP
OF THE ICEBERG.

13:08.710 --> 13:09.847
- WOW.

13:09.890 --> 13:12.199
- OH, THE PRESERVATIVES
IN THOSE THINGS ARE TERRIBLE.

13:12.230 --> 13:16.439
- OH. YEAH. NO, UH, NORMALLY,
I BAKE THEM FROM SCRATCH.

13:16.480 --> 13:18.402
- OH, YEAH. WE DO A TON
OF BAKING AROUND HERE.

13:18.450 --> 13:21.578
- WE HAD A MOST AMAZING
TIME MAKING COOKIES,

13:21.620 --> 13:22.587
DIDN'T WE, GIRLS?

13:22.620 --> 13:24.690
- OH, YEAH!
- MM-HMM.

13:24.730 --> 13:25.719
- HI.
- HI.

13:25.770 --> 13:29.035
- OH, HEY, JOELSKIES TELLS ME
YOU'RE A LAWYER.

13:29.080 --> 13:31.969
- "JOELSKIES" IS CORRECT.
YEAH, I AM.

13:32.010 --> 13:33.693
- THAT'S GREAT.
- THANKS.

13:33.740 --> 13:34.946
- THERE'S A DAD
IN MRS. ABRAMAR'S CLASS

13:34.980 --> 13:36.117
WHO'S A LAWYER.

13:36.160 --> 13:38.663
HE SOLD 20 BOOKS OF RAFFLE
TICKETS IN ONE AFTERNOON.

13:38.710 --> 13:41.531
HERE. I'M GONNA GIVE YOU TEN,
YOU KNOW, JUST TO START OUT.

13:41.570 --> 13:43.197
- YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA SAY HI
TO MY DAUGHTER.

13:43.230 --> 13:45.198
- OH, NO. YOU KNOW WHAT,
WE'RE GOING. NO, COME ON.

13:45.230 --> 13:46.640
HARMONY, HONEY, WE'RE GOING.

13:46.680 --> 13:47.920
WE'RE GONNA LET SYDNEY SEE
HER MOMMY.

13:47.960 --> 13:49.370
SHE HARDLY EVER GETS
TO SEE HER.

13:49.410 --> 13:50.923
DON'T FORGET YOUR WORRY BEADS,
SWEETH EART.

13:50.960 --> 13:53.611
WE'RE BUDDHISTS.

13:53.660 --> 13:55.582
HERE YOU GO.
OKAY, WE'RE GOING.

13:55.620 --> 13:56.757
JOEL.
- HEY.

13:56.800 --> 14:00.588
OH. YOU ARE SO AMAZING.
- OH. ALL RIGHTY.

14:00.630 --> 14:03.144
- AND SYDNEY, SWEETHEART,
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

14:03.180 --> 14:05.557
WO AI NI.
- WO YE AI NI.

14:05.600 --> 14:08.808
- OH. I JUST SAID "I LOVE YOU"
TO HER IN MANDARIN

14:08.840 --> 14:10.876
AND SHE SAID
"I LOVE YOU TOO."

14:10.910 --> 14:13.674
OH. I COULD
EAT YOU UP.

14:13.710 --> 14:15.393
- ALL RIGHTY, GIRLS.
- OKAY, BYE.

14:15.440 --> 14:16.771
- BYE.
- BYE-BYE.

14:16.820 --> 14:18.640
- SEE YOU, GIRLS.
- BYE.

14:18.680 --> 14:19.533
- HEY.
- HI.

14:19.580 --> 14:21.855
- YOUR LIFE IS ABOUT TO CHANGE
FOREVER.

14:21.890 --> 14:23.573
- IT'S ALL ABOUT ACCEPTING,
NOT RESISTING.

14:23.620 --> 14:25.474
- IF YOU PUT IN THE WORK,
THEY'LL DO GREAT.

14:25.510 --> 14:29.276
- NOEL IS DOING FANTASTIC.
- WELL, MAX HASN'T--

14:29.310 --> 14:31.961
HASN'T EVEN BEEN DIAGNOSED YET
SO WE'RE--WE'RE NOT EVEN SURE

14:32.000 --> 14:33.274
IF HE HAS ASPERGER'S.

14:33.320 --> 14:35.003
- RAH!
- WELL, DENIAL'S VERY COMMON.

14:35.040 --> 14:36.655
SO WHAT HAVE YOU GUYS DONE
SO FAR?

14:36.700 --> 14:37.974
HAVE YOU CHANGED MAX'S
DIET YET?

14:38.010 --> 14:40.626
- UM...
- WE NEED TO CHANGE HIS DIET?

14:40.670 --> 14:41.944
- OH, GOD, YES.
GLUTEN-FREE.

14:41.980 --> 14:43.766
NO WHEAT. NO SUGAR.
NO CHEMICALS.

14:43.810 --> 14:44.834
- CASEIN-FREE TOO.
- WHAT'S CASEIN?

14:44.880 --> 14:45.869
- I DON'T KNOW.

14:45.910 --> 14:47.184
- WE HAVE A NUTRITIONIST
THAT YOU ARE GONNA LOVE.

14:47.230 --> 14:48.629
PHILLY, GET THE CARDS.
- OKAY.

14:48.680 --> 14:50.887
- GOOD. YOU'RE ALSO GOING
TO NEED AN O.T. AND A P.T.

14:50.920 --> 14:52.706
- A P.T.?
I DON'T KNOW WHAT A P.T. IS.

14:52.750 --> 14:54.672
- A P.T.'S
A PHYSICAL THERAPIST.

14:54.720 --> 14:55.641
- THERE YOU GO.
- THANK YOU, LOVER.

14:55.680 --> 14:57.989
COLORED INDEX CARDS.
THEY'RE A LIFESAVER.

14:58.030 --> 14:59.406
- THERE IS SO MUCH
TO KEEP TRACK OF.

14:59.450 --> 15:01.759
- AH! OUR ENTIRE LIVES
ARE ON THESE CARDS.

15:01.790 --> 15:03.894
RED IS DIET.
YELLOW IS THERAPIES.

15:03.930 --> 15:05.989
GREEN IS MEDS.
BLUE IS AIDES AND RESPITE.

15:06.040 --> 15:08.691
- DON'T FORGET ABOUT PINK.
- OH, MY GOD. PINK.

15:08.730 --> 15:09.765
PINK IS OUR SEX LIFE.

15:09.800 --> 15:10.835
IF WE DIDN'T HAVE A CARD
FOR IT,

15:10.870 --> 15:11.859
IT WOULD GO STRAIGHT
INTO THE CRAPPER

15:11.910 --> 15:13.138
WITH EVERYTHING
THAT'S GOING ON.

15:13.180 --> 15:14.283
- HEY, ISN'T IT TUESDAY?

15:14.320 --> 15:15.878
- [laughs] OH, MY GOD.
HE'S AN ANIMAL.

15:15.910 --> 15:17.047
UM, EVENTUALLY--
EVENTUALLY,

15:17.080 --> 15:18.422
YOU'RE GOING TO NEED
AN IN-HOUSE AIDE.

15:18.460 --> 15:19.427
- OH, AND A BEHAVIORIST.

15:19.470 --> 15:20.801
- I DON'T--
WHAT'S A BEHAVIORIST?

15:20.850 --> 15:22.329
I'VE NEVER--
- A BEHAVIORAL THERAPIST.

15:22.360 --> 15:24.988
A GREAT BEHAVIORAL THERAPIST
WILL CHANGE MAX'S LIFE.

15:25.020 --> 15:27.159
- OH, THEY SAY DR. PELIKAN
IS THE BEST.

15:27.200 --> 15:29.259
A MIRACLE WORKER.
- A BEHAVIORIST?

15:29.300 --> 15:30.267
- MM-HMM.

15:30.300 --> 15:31.881
- SO, UH, HE WORKS
AT CHANGING BEHAVIOR.

15:31.930 --> 15:33.124
THAT COULD BE GOOD.

15:33.170 --> 15:34.239
THAT COULD HELP MAX

15:34.270 --> 15:35.680
MAYBE GET OUT
OF HIS PIRATE COSTUME.

15:35.720 --> 15:36.926
- FORGET ABOUT PELIKAN.
- WHY?

15:36.970 --> 15:38.824
- BECAUSE NO ONE GETS IN
TO SEE PELIKAN.

15:38.860 --> 15:40.031
HE'S AN ELUSIVE ASS.

15:40.070 --> 15:42.038
HE'S LIKE THE BOB DYLAN
OF AUTISM.

15:42.070 --> 15:43.583
- YOU KNOW WHAT,
I WANT TO GIVE THIS A SHOT.

15:43.630 --> 15:46.519
I-I MAY HAVE SOME CONNECTIONS.
SO HOW DO YOU SPELL THAT?

15:46.560 --> 15:48.209
P-E-L?
- PELIKAN.

15:48.250 --> 15:51.378
both: LIKE THE BIRD.
BUT WITH A "K".

15:51.430 --> 15:52.874
- WE MADE DINNER.
STAY FOR DINNER.

15:52.910 --> 15:54.184
- STAY FOR DINNER.
WE ALREADY MADE--

15:54.220 --> 15:55.289
WELL, WE DIDN'T MAKE IT.

15:55.330 --> 15:56.706
- OH, NO, NO.
REALLY, WE HAVE TO--

15:56.740 --> 15:58.435
- I GOT TO PREHEAT THE OVEN.
- IT'S GLUTEN-FREE PASTA.

15:58.470 --> 15:59.983
IT'S REALLY GOOD.
- IT'S ACTUALLY GOOD.

16:00.020 --> 16:01.601
YOU SHOULD GET USED TO IT.
- NO, NO, NO.

16:01.650 --> 16:03.197
- NONSENSE.
YOU'RE PART OF THE FAMILY NOW.

16:03.230 --> 16:04.470
WE'RE SO--
- WELCOME.

16:04.510 --> 16:06.262
- WELCOME.
- WELCOME TO THE FAMILY.

16:06.310 --> 16:08.926
- WE'RE HAPPY TO HAVE YOU.
SIT DOWN.

16:08.960 --> 16:10.996
[loud guitar strumming]

16:14.210 --> 16:16.678
[rock music playing]

16:17.970 --> 16:20.074
- [snaps photo]
OKAY. I SENT IT.

16:20.110 --> 16:21.554
CAN YOU BELIEVE
I GOT AN INTERVIEW?

16:21.600 --> 16:23.761
- THAT'S FANTASTIC.
I GOT YOUR EMAIL.

16:23.810 --> 16:26.631
- OH. AND?

16:26.670 --> 16:27.739
- IT'S A LITTLE...

16:27.770 --> 16:29.214
- I THOUGHT--I THOUGHT
I WAS BEING HOT CORPORATE.

16:29.260 --> 16:31.421
WHAT--WHAT--
WHAT DO THEY WANT?

16:31.470 --> 16:34.155
- YOU NEED TO GO IN THERE
AND SAY "HERE I AM.

16:34.200 --> 16:35.770
I'M THE ONLY ONE
THAT COULD DO THIS JOB."

16:35.820 --> 16:36.741
- WELL, THAT'S A LIE.

16:36.780 --> 16:37.337
EVERYONE ELSE
COULD DO THIS JOB BUT ME.

16:37.370 --> 16:38.405
I'M NOT EVEN QUALIFIED.

16:38.440 --> 16:39.361
- WELL, THAT'S PROBABLY NOT
THE BEST ATTITUDE.

16:39.410 --> 16:42.334
YOU NEED TO SPIN A LITTLE.
- I CAN'T SPIN.

16:42.380 --> 16:44.951
I LOST MY SPIN.
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO SPIN.

16:45.000 --> 16:46.206
- GREAT, THANKS.
- MAY I SPIN?

16:46.240 --> 16:47.377
- PLEASE.
- YOU'RE A GREAT ARTIST.

16:47.420 --> 16:49.376
YOU'VE BEEN UNAVAILABLE
FOR A WHILE SO YOU'RE A FIND.

16:49.420 --> 16:50.557
YOU'VE BEEN DOING
OTHER THINGS.

16:50.590 --> 16:52.000
- CHECKING MY EX-HUSBAND
INTO REHAB.

16:52.040 --> 16:53.348
- NOW YOU'RE BACK
IN THE EAST BAY

16:53.390 --> 16:54.721
AND YOU'RE READY TO PICK UP
WHERE YOU LEFT OFF.

16:54.770 --> 16:56.624
- TO MOVE IN WITH MY PARENTS
AT AN INAPPROPRIATE AGE.

16:56.670 --> 16:57.898
- YOU'RE NOT HELPING.

16:57.940 --> 17:00.215
- I JUST CAN'T SEE
REALLY GETTING THIS JOB.

17:00.260 --> 17:01.943
- THEY CALLED YOU,
DIDN'T THEY?

17:01.980 --> 17:03.356
- I KNOW.
THAT'S THE AMAZING THING.

17:03.400 --> 17:05.459
ALL I DID WAS SEND MY WORK,
AND THEY CALLED.

17:05.500 --> 17:07.639
- WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE
THEY SEE YOUR TALENT.

17:07.680 --> 17:08.601
THAT'S STEP ONE.

17:08.640 --> 17:10.437
STEP TWO IS YOU LOOK THIS GUY
IN THE EYE

17:10.470 --> 17:13.359
AND YOU SAY, "I AM GOING
TO BLOW YOUR FREAKIN' MIND."

17:13.410 --> 17:17.028
- [laughs] IT SOUNDS GOOD
WHEN YOU SAY IT.

17:17.070 --> 17:19.026
DID YOU GET THAT ONE?

17:19.070 --> 17:20.822
- I THINK
WE'RE IN THE WRONG STORE.

17:20.860 --> 17:24.899
- OH. CRAP.

17:24.940 --> 17:28.649
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?

17:28.700 --> 17:30.452
OKAY, YOU DON'T LIKE IT.
I HAVE OTHERS.

17:30.490 --> 17:32.458
LET ME TRY THEM ON.
- NO, NO, NO. KATIE. KATIE.

17:32.490 --> 17:34.697
LISTEN, UM...

17:34.740 --> 17:37.664
I DON'T KNOW IF IT'S GOING
TO WORK OUT THIS WEEKEND.

17:37.710 --> 17:39.223
- WHAT?
- I KNOW.

17:39.260 --> 17:42.366
- NO, WHAT? WHAT--WHAT--
WHAT COULD'VE COME UP?

17:42.400 --> 17:45.460
- WELL, IT'S KIND
OF A BIG DEAL.

17:45.510 --> 17:48.399
I-I DON'T KNOW IF I WANT TO GO
INTO IT RIGHT NOW.

17:48.440 --> 17:51.785
- CROSBY, IF YOU'RE BACK WITH
THAT BIMBO WAITRESS, BRANDI,

17:51.820 --> 17:54.641
OR THAT PSEUDO-ACTIVIST,
WAIFY ACTRESS PERSON--

17:54.690 --> 17:56.089
- OKAY, HONEY, HONEY,
I'M NOT BACK WITH ANYONE.

17:56.140 --> 17:58.062
- JUST TELL ME THE TRUTH.

18:00.700 --> 18:03.214
- OKAY.
[clears throat]

18:03.250 --> 18:07.937
OKAY.
[sighs]

18:07.980 --> 18:10.949
WE THINK MAX HAS ASPERGER'S.

18:10.980 --> 18:12.083
- WHAT?

18:12.120 --> 18:13.257
- ADAM AND KRISTINA

18:13.290 --> 18:14.359
ARE JUST FINDING OUT ABOUT IT.

18:14.400 --> 18:16.493
AND I FEEL LIKE I SHOULD
STICK AROUND THIS WEEKEND

18:16.540 --> 18:20.089
TO BE THERE FOR ADAM
AND KRISTINA.

18:20.130 --> 18:22.883
AND THE LITTLE GUY.

18:26.550 --> 18:31.203
- IT'S AMAZING TO HEAR YOU
TALK LIKE THAT.

18:31.240 --> 18:35.518
YOU'RE GONNA BE AN AMAZING
FATHER ONE DAY.

18:35.560 --> 18:38.381
AW, COME HERE.

18:38.420 --> 18:40.388
I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND
IF YOU NEED

18:40.420 --> 18:42.809
TO POSTPONE THE WEEKEND.

18:46.260 --> 18:48.490
- YOU KNOW, IT--
IT'S NOT IN STONE THOUGH.

18:48.540 --> 18:51.498
AND WE SHOULD PROBABLY
KEEP THAT OPTION OPEN.

18:51.540 --> 18:53.269
- [laughs]

18:53.300 --> 18:55.188
- DID YOU KNOW A COCKROACH
CAN HOLD ITS BREATH

18:55.230 --> 18:56.674
FOR 40 MINUTES?

18:56.720 --> 18:58.438
- FASCINATING.

18:58.480 --> 19:00.573
- ALL RIGHT, MAX, I WANT YOU
TO PUT CHARLIE AWAY.

19:00.620 --> 19:01.689
IT'S DINNER TIME.

19:01.720 --> 19:04.473
- COCKROACH CAN LIVE A MONTH
WITHOUT ITS HEAD.

19:04.520 --> 19:07.512
- OKAY, SERIOUSLY, I'M--
I DON'T HAVE AN APPETITE.

19:07.560 --> 19:09.448
- HADDIE, IT'S FINE.
IT'S NOT THAT BIG OF A DEAL.

19:09.490 --> 19:14.143
- ALL RIGHT, YOU KNOW WHAT,
MAX, PLEASE EAT YOUR FOOD.

19:14.180 --> 19:15.659
LEAVE THE COCKROACH ALONE.

19:15.700 --> 19:16.621
- I DON'T LIKE IT.

19:16.670 --> 19:17.523
- WELL, HOW DO YOU KNOW
YOU DON'T LIKE IT

19:17.570 --> 19:18.764
IF YOU'VE NEVER TRIED IT?

19:18.810 --> 19:19.595
- IT'S NOT ONE OF HIS FOODS.

19:19.640 --> 19:21.392
- HEY, MAX, SWEETHEART,
YOU KNOW,

19:21.430 --> 19:23.182
MAYBE YOU COULD EARN
SOME TV TIME TONIGHT

19:23.230 --> 19:24.367
BY TRYING YOUR FOOD.

19:24.400 --> 19:25.879
- I GET TV AFTER DINNER
ANYWAY.

19:25.920 --> 19:26.944
- IF YOU DON'T EAT
YOUR DINNER

19:26.990 --> 19:27.979
THEN YOU WON'T GET TV TIME.

19:28.020 --> 19:29.123
- IT'S NOT FAIR.

19:29.160 --> 19:30.843
THE RULES ARE I GET AN HOUR
OF TV TIME AFTER DINNER.

19:30.890 --> 19:32.050
- THE BOOK SAYS THAT WE SHOULD
FRAME THINGS FOR A REWARD,

19:32.100 --> 19:33.124
NOT PUNISHMENT.

19:33.170 --> 19:34.956
- WELL, HE'S SAYING
HE ALREADY GETS TV ANYWAY.

19:35.000 --> 19:37.025
- THAT IS MY TIME FOR THE TV.

19:37.070 --> 19:39.470
- MAYBE--MAYBE YOU GUYS
COULD GIVE HIM EXTRA TV TIME.

19:39.520 --> 19:41.135
- YEAH, HOW ABOUT THAT?
HOW ABOUT THAT, MAX?

19:41.180 --> 19:43.796
HOW ABOUT IF YOU TRY YOUR FOOD,
YOU'LL GET EXTRA TV TIME?

19:43.830 --> 19:44.694
- HOW MUCH?
- AN HOUR.

19:44.730 --> 19:46.072
- FIVE MINUTES.
- WHAT YOUR MOTHER SAID.

19:46.110 --> 19:47.486
FIVE MINUTES.
- FORGET IT.

19:47.530 --> 19:52.149
- PER BITE.
' 1! 2/ 3! 4/ 5/

19:52.190 --> 19:55.944
6, 7, 8,

19:55.980 --> 19:59.529
9, 10, 11, 12.

19:59.570 --> 20:01.606
THAT'S AN HOUR, RIGHT?
YOU SAID.

20:01.640 --> 20:05.531
- YEAH. WAIT, MAX,
YOU HAVE TO SIT DOWN

20:05.580 --> 20:07.195
UNTIL WE'RE FINISHED
WITH OUR MEAL.

20:07.240 --> 20:10.539
- WHY? I ALREADY EARNED
MY TV TIME.

20:10.580 --> 20:13.708
- THAT WORKED OUT WELL.
- SHUT UP, SWEETIE.

20:16.560 --> 20:18.175
I HAVE EMAILED
EVERYONE I KNOW

20:18.210 --> 20:21.520
LOOKING FOR A CONNECTION
WITH DR. PELIKAN.

20:21.560 --> 20:24.176
IT'S LIKE TRYING TO MEET
THE POPE.

20:24.220 --> 20:26.040
- THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOMEBODY ELSE.

20:26.080 --> 20:27.069
- I DON'T KNOW.

20:27.120 --> 20:29.873
[possum scampering]

20:29.910 --> 20:32.219
THAT ARROGANT SON OF A BITCH.

20:42.750 --> 20:45.822
[opossum chirping]

20:47.410 --> 20:49.719
[bushes rustling]

20:49.760 --> 20:54.038
[opossum chirping]

21:09.610 --> 21:11.635
- WHAT?
- I FOUND THIS IN THE BACK.

21:11.680 --> 21:16.128
- AND...?
- AND IS IT YOURS?

21:16.170 --> 21:17.398
- NO.
- YOU SURE?

21:17.440 --> 21:18.543
- HADDIE?
- NO!

21:18.580 --> 21:20.684
- I SWEAR TO GOD, IF YOU'RE
LYING TO US RIGHT NOW--

21:20.720 --> 21:21.857
- DON'T LIE.
- DO NOT LIE TO ME.

21:21.900 --> 21:24.107
YOU ARE DIGGING YOURSELF
A VERY, VERY, VERY DEEP HOLE.

21:24.140 --> 21:25.619
- BE THE WORST THING
YOU COULD DO.

21:25.660 --> 21:29.835
- YOU GUYS...
THIS IS NOT MINE.

21:30.970 --> 21:32.597
- NO?
- NO.

21:32.630 --> 21:34.598
- NO? 100%?
- YEAH.

21:34.630 --> 21:36.803
- POSITIVE.
- YEAH.

21:36.840 --> 21:38.569
- ALL RIGHT.
- OKAY.

21:38.600 --> 21:40.739
- BUT IT FEELS GOOD
THAT YOU TRUST YOUR DAUGHTER.

21:40.780 --> 21:42.941
- SORRY.
- YEAH.

21:45.640 --> 21:50.407
- WOW, YOU DID THIS IN 1990.
- YEAH.

21:50.440 --> 21:52.886
YOU WERE PROBABLY
IN GRADE SCHOOL.

21:52.930 --> 21:54.409
- PRESCHOOL, ACTUALLY.

21:54.450 --> 21:57.203
- OH, WOW.
THAT'S DEPRESSING.

21:57.240 --> 21:58.719
FOR ME. I MEAN, FOR ME.
NOT FOR YOU.

21:58.760 --> 22:00.864
FOR YOU, LOOK AT YOU.
THAT'S--YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

22:00.900 --> 22:04.654
- UH, SO WHAT HAVE YOU
BEEN DOING ALL THESE YEARS?

22:04.700 --> 22:05.962
- WELL, I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
ASK THAT.

22:06.010 --> 22:09.218
UM, I'VE JUST...

22:09.250 --> 22:10.831
BEEN FOCUSING ON MY FAMILY,
I GUESS.

22:10.880 --> 22:13.496
I HAVE TWO KIDS.
- UM, YEAH, THAT'S WONDERFUL.

22:13.530 --> 22:16.294
- NOT IF YOU KNOW THEM.
I'M KIDDING. THEY'RE GREAT.

22:17.710 --> 22:19.678
NO, WHAT I MEANT TO SAY
IS THAT IT'S AN HONORABLE CHOICE

22:19.710 --> 22:21.507
TO CHOOSE YOUR FAMILY
OVER CAREER.

22:21.540 --> 22:23.986
- YEAH.
I JUST MOVED TO BERKELEY.

22:24.030 --> 22:26.169
AND THIS MIGHT SOUND LAME,

22:26.200 --> 22:28.782
BUT I'M READY TO MAKE
A FRESH START.

22:28.830 --> 22:32.823
AND IF YOU GIVE ME
THIS CHANCE,

22:32.860 --> 22:36.341
I KNOW I CAN BLOW
YOUR FREAKIN' MIND.

22:36.380 --> 22:38.007
UGH. MY SISTER TOLD ME
TO SAY THAT.

22:38.040 --> 22:40.008
THAT SOUNDED SO STUPID.
I'M REALLY SORRY.

22:40.040 --> 22:42.281
- THAT'S OKAY. THAT'S OKAY.
NOW, UH, TELL ME ABOUT THIS.

22:42.320 --> 22:43.309
WHAT AM I LOOKING AT HERE?

22:43.360 --> 22:46.705
- OKAY, SO, UM, MY EX-HUSBAND
WAS IN A BAND.

22:46.740 --> 22:47.832
AND, UH,
IT WAS PRETTY SUCCESSFUL.

22:47.880 --> 22:50.189
AND I STARTED DOING
ALL THEIR, UM,

22:50.230 --> 22:51.674
THEIR POSTERS AND STUFF.

22:51.710 --> 22:53.917
AND THEN I WORKED
FOR ANOTHER BAND.

22:53.950 --> 22:57.260
AND WORD GOT OUT
TO SOME RESTAURANTS SO...

22:57.300 --> 22:59.928
- RIGHT. UH, WELL, I GOT TO BE
HONEST WITH YOU, SARAH,

22:59.960 --> 23:03.168
YOUR WORK IS PHENOMENAL.

23:03.200 --> 23:05.065
WOW.
- REALLY?

23:05.100 --> 23:06.271
- I LOVE THESE.

23:06.310 --> 23:07.959
IT--IT--IT'S HIP
WITHOUT TRYING TO BE HIP.

23:08.000 --> 23:08.967
IT'S FRESH, FUN.

23:09.000 --> 23:10.513
NOW, YOU SAW THE RANGE

23:10.560 --> 23:12.619
THAT WE'RE TALKING
FOR STARTING SALARY.

23:12.660 --> 23:15.106
- THE MONEY? YEAH.
THAT WOULD BE FINE.

23:15.150 --> 23:19.143
- GOOD. GOOD.
UM, YOU'LL BE REPORTING TO ME.

23:19.190 --> 23:20.498
IS THAT GONNA BE A PROBLEM?

23:20.530 --> 23:23.283
JUST IN TERMS OF THE, UH...

23:23.330 --> 23:25.423
- 'CAUSE I'M SO OLD?
- THAT I'M SO YOUNG.

23:25.470 --> 23:27.700
- NO, THAT I'M SO OLD.
- OH. NO, THAT'S--

23:27.750 --> 23:28.819
- NO, NO, THAT'S FINE.

23:28.850 --> 23:31.910
I CAN TAKE A NOTE
FROM A WHIPPERSNAPPER LIKE YOU.

23:31.960 --> 23:34.815
UGH. I, UH, NO,
IT WOULDN'T BE ANY PROBLEM.

23:34.860 --> 23:39.684
- OKAY. GOOD. ALL RIGHT.
THAT'S GOOD.

23:39.720 --> 23:43.611
- I REALLY WANT THIS JOB.

23:58.540 --> 24:01.532
- HI.
- HEY, YOU'RE A HOT MOM.

24:01.570 --> 24:04.016
- [laughs] HI.
- [laughs] HI.

24:04.060 --> 24:06.199
- OH. WHERE'S SYDNEY?
- UH, SHE'S NOT HERE.

24:06.230 --> 24:07.436
- WHAT?
- SHE'S ON HER WAY.

24:07.480 --> 24:09.095
SHE'S IN A CAR
WITH RACQUEL AND HARMONY.

24:09.130 --> 24:10.927
- RACQUEL? WHY?

24:10.960 --> 24:13.440
- MANDARIN CLASS RAN OVER,
AND THEY NEEDED SOMEBODY

24:13.480 --> 24:14.993
TO CLAIM A TABLE.

24:15.030 --> 24:17.100
IT'S GONNA BE
A PRETTY BIG GROUP.

24:17.140 --> 24:20.268
- OH.
- YES?

24:20.320 --> 24:22.527
- I MOVED MY MEETING
AND JOCKEYED THROUGH TRAFFIC

24:22.560 --> 24:24.937
TO HAVE 21 MINUTES
WITH MY DAUGHTER,

24:24.980 --> 24:28.939
AND SHE'S IN THE CAR
WITH RACQUEL.

24:28.980 --> 24:31.596
- I'LL TEXT HER.
- NO. SHE'S AN INSANE DRIVER.

24:31.640 --> 24:33.733
DON'T TEXT HER.
- OH, JULIA.

24:33.780 --> 24:35.941
- SHE IS.
- OH, GOD, JULES.

24:35.990 --> 24:38.629
I KNOW YOU THINK RACQUEL
IS INTENSE.

24:38.680 --> 24:40.910
AND SHE IS.
BUT SHE'S--SHE'S A GREAT MOM.

24:40.960 --> 24:43.611
- GOOD.
THAT'S GREAT TO HEAR.

24:43.650 --> 24:45.402
- CONSIDERING.
- MOMMY!

24:45.440 --> 24:48.580
- HI, SYD!
OKAY, I HAVE 18 MINUTES.

24:48.620 --> 24:50.167
I'M SPENDING THEM
WITH MY DAUGHTER.

24:50.210 --> 24:51.689
- OKAY.
- HI, BABY. COME HERE!

24:51.730 --> 24:52.799
- HI.
- HEY. HEY, GUYS.

24:52.830 --> 24:54.934
- YOU MISSED
THE MOST AMAZING CLASS.

24:54.970 --> 24:56.892
- YEAH?

24:56.940 --> 25:00.216
- SO YOU DROVE
ALL THE WAY FROM DOWNTOWN

25:00.250 --> 25:01.285
TO ASK ME THIS?

25:01.320 --> 25:03.697
- COULD YOU JUST ANSWER ME?

25:03.740 --> 25:05.947
- NO, IT'S NOT MY POT.
- ARE YOU SURE?

25:05.980 --> 25:07.083
- YEAH, WELL, HEY,
YOU KNOW,

25:07.120 --> 25:08.872
I HAVEN'T SMOKED THAT STUFF
IN YEARS.

25:08.920 --> 25:09.944
AND, UH, WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU DOING

25:09.990 --> 25:11.844
OUT IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE NIGHT WEED WHACKING?

25:13.020 --> 25:16.433
IT'S A POSSUM, RAT, RACCOON.
I DON'T KNOW. SOMETHING.

25:16.480 --> 25:19.745
- CALL AN EXTERMINATOR.
- IT'S PERSONAL.

25:19.790 --> 25:20.950
- PERSONAL?
- YEAH.

25:21.000 --> 25:22.399
EVERY NIGHT,
HE'S UP ON THE ROOF

25:22.450 --> 25:23.758
MAKING NOISE RIGHT ABOVE US.

25:23.790 --> 25:25.417
AND JUST FEELS LIKE IT'S
DELIBERATE.

25:25.450 --> 25:28.032
LIKE HE'S...
MOCKING ME.

25:28.070 --> 25:29.105
SO ANYWAY, I GOT TO GET RID
OF IT.

25:29.140 --> 25:30.243
I GOT TO GET IT OUT
OF THE HOUSE. THAT'S ALL.

25:30.280 --> 25:32.862
- WELL, SONNY, YOU KNOW,
IT COULD BE SOMETHING ELSE.

25:34.420 --> 25:36.308
- LIKE WHAT, A WEASEL?
- WEASEL?

25:36.360 --> 25:37.804
NO, PSYCHOLOGICAL.
COULD BE...

25:37.840 --> 25:40.047
- IT'S NOT PSYCHOLOGICAL.
- SOMETHING YOU'RE MANIFESTING.

25:40.090 --> 25:41.739
- I'M NOT MANIFESTING ANYTHING,
OKAY?

25:41.780 --> 25:44.226
- WELL, YOU'RE CERTAINLY KIND
OF RESISTANT TO THE IDEA...

25:44.260 --> 25:45.875
- HEY.
- HEY, ADAM, PERFECT.

25:45.920 --> 25:47.399
MOM JUST MADE CARROT CAKE.

25:47.440 --> 25:50.329
- OH, GOOD.
- PSYCHOLOGICAL.

25:50.370 --> 25:51.746
- POP, CARROT CAKE?

25:51.790 --> 25:53.439
- UH, YEAH,
MAYBE IN A LITTLE BIT.

25:53.480 --> 25:54.572
GOT A LITTLE MORE WORK
TO DO.

25:54.620 --> 25:55.996
WOULDN'T WANT TO HELP,
WOULD YOU?

25:56.030 --> 25:57.440
- OKAY. YEAH. EARN IT.
- YEAH.

25:57.480 --> 25:58.788
- YEAH, MAKE SURE YOU EARN IT.
- YEAH.

25:58.830 --> 26:00.969
- DID YOU DITCH A BAG OF WEED
IN MY YARD?

26:01.000 --> 26:04.310
- ARE YOU CRAZY?
- JUST ASKING A QUESTION.

26:04.350 --> 26:06.580
- HMM. BY THE WAY,

26:06.630 --> 26:08.723
I NEED YOU TO COVER FOR ME
WITH KATIE.

26:08.770 --> 26:10.214
I TOLD HER MAX HAS ASPERGER'S

26:10.250 --> 26:12.901
AND THAT'S WHY I CAN'T GO AWAY
WITH HER THIS WEEKEND.

26:12.950 --> 26:14.941
- YOU USED MAX'S ASPERGER'S
AS AN EXCUSE.

26:14.980 --> 26:16.356
- YEAH, I'M DOUBLE-BOOKED.

26:16.400 --> 26:18.322
I'M SUPPOSED TO GO WITH KATIE
TO THIS INCREDIBLE SPA

26:18.360 --> 26:19.839
IN NAPA
AND THEN JASMINE ASKS ME

26:19.880 --> 26:21.120
IF I CAN BOND WITH JABBAR.

26:21.160 --> 26:22.570
- SO YOU'RE DECIDING
WHETHER OR NOT

26:22.610 --> 26:23.986
TO GO TO SOME SPA
WITH KATIE

26:24.030 --> 26:25.577
OR SPEND TIME
WITH YOUR SON

26:25.610 --> 26:26.747
THAT YOU'VE MET TWICE
IN YOUR LIFE.

26:26.790 --> 26:28.781
- IF YOU SAW THE LINGERIE
SHE BOUGHT FOR THIS TRIP,

26:28.820 --> 26:30.026
YOU'D UNDERSTAND THE DILEMMA.

26:30.070 --> 26:31.856
- HEY, JACKASS,
YOU HAVE A SON, OKAY?

26:31.900 --> 26:34.653
YOU NEED TO MAN UP, TAKE CARE
OF YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES.

26:34.690 --> 26:36.339
- MM. YOU COMFORTABLE
UP THERE ON YOUR HIGH HORSE

26:36.380 --> 26:37.688
LOOKING DOWN ON ME?

26:37.730 --> 26:41.143
MY LIFE'S COMPLICATED,
ADAM.

26:41.180 --> 26:42.624
MM. LISTEN, BY THE WAY,

26:42.670 --> 26:43.932
THAT GUY
THAT YOU EMAILED ME ABOUT--

26:43.980 --> 26:47.632
DR. PELIKAN--
I GOT AN IN.

26:47.670 --> 26:48.705
- YOU?
- YEAH, ME.

26:48.740 --> 26:50.662
I HAVE AN IN.
CAN YOU IMAGINE?

26:50.710 --> 26:55.124
KATIE'S MOM DID HIM
AT SOME NEW AGE RETREAT

26:55.160 --> 26:56.058
BACK IN THE '705.

26:56.090 --> 26:57.648
- SLOW DOWN. WHAT?

26:57.680 --> 27:01.719
- KATIE'S MOM DID HIM
AT ESALIN IN 1973, OKAY?

27:01.750 --> 27:03.024
- AND THIS HELPS ME HOW?

27:03.060 --> 27:05.267
- HE HAS A CANCELLATION
THIS AFTERNOON.

27:05.310 --> 27:06.686
- HE HAS A CANCELLATION TODAY?

27:06.720 --> 27:08.347
WHY DID YOU WAIT SO LONG
TO TELL ME ABOUT THIS?

27:08.380 --> 27:11.201
- WELL, SORRY THAT I WANTED
TO TALK TO YOU FOR FIVE SECONDS

27:11.250 --> 27:12.103
ABOUT MY LIFE.

27:12.140 --> 27:13.209
- I GOT TO GO, OKAY?

27:13.250 --> 27:14.899
THIS GUY'S IMPOSSIBLE TO SEE.
THANK YOU.

27:14.940 --> 27:17.079
- OH, GREAT.
THANKS FOR YOUR TIME.

27:17.110 --> 27:18.418
THAT'S REALLY GENEROUS
OF YOU.

27:18.460 --> 27:19.973
- I DON'T WANT TO GO.

27:20.010 --> 27:22.114
- LOOK, MAX, WE'RE JUMPING OVER
AN 18-MONTH WAITING LIST HERE.

27:22.150 --> 27:23.139
OKAY, WE HAVE TO GO.

27:23.190 --> 27:25.044
- HONEY, HE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT A WAITING LIST IS.

27:25.090 --> 27:26.284
- THIS GUY IS THE BOB DYLAN
OF ASPERGER'S.

27:26.330 --> 27:28.150
- BOB DYLAN NEVER HAD
A NUMBER ONE RECORD.

27:28.190 --> 27:29.361
- HE'S A GENIUS.

27:29.400 --> 27:31.265
- THEN HOW COME HE NEVER HAD
A NUMBER ONE HIT RECORD

27:31.300 --> 27:32.267
ON BILLBOARD?

27:32.300 --> 27:33.915
THE BEATLES HAD 20 NUMBER ONE
HIT RECORDS.

27:33.960 --> 27:35.928
- UH-HUH.
- MICHAEL JACKSON HAD 13.

27:35.960 --> 27:37.439
THE BEE GEES HAD NINE.

27:37.480 --> 27:39.789
- WELL, MAYBE TRY NOT TO COMPARE
BOB DYLAN TO THE BEE GEES.

27:39.830 --> 27:41.513
AND WE HAVE TO GO.

27:41.550 --> 27:43.415
- HEY, TURN THE TV BACK ON.
- WE HAVE TO GO, MAX.

27:43.450 --> 27:44.610
COME ON.
- NO WAY.

27:44.660 --> 27:45.934
- OKAY, RIGHT NOW,
WE HAVE TO DO THIS.

27:45.970 --> 27:47.722
- NO!
- MAX, PUT YOUR SHOES ON.

27:47.760 --> 27:49.204
- MAX. HEY. MAX!

27:49.250 --> 27:50.626
THIS GUY CAN'T HELP YOU
UNLESS WE GO.

27:50.660 --> 27:52.070
- NOT THAT YOU NEED HELP.
- WE NEED TO GO.

27:52.110 --> 27:53.099
YES, HE DOES.

27:53.150 --> 27:54.492
- ADAM, I DON'T WANT HIM
TO THINK THAT HE NEEDS--

27:54.530 --> 27:56.350
- KRISTINA, WE NEED TO MAKE
THIS APPOINTMENT, OKAY?

27:56.390 --> 27:58.597
[all arguing]
- HEY.

27:58.640 --> 28:02.019
- WHAT? WHAT?
- UM...

28:02.050 --> 28:05.326
IT WAS MINE.
THE POT. IT WAS MINE.

28:05.370 --> 28:08.157
UM...I JUST COULDN'T SLEEP
LAST NIGHT.

28:08.200 --> 28:10.088
AND I FELT LIKE I HAD
TO TELL YOU.

28:10.130 --> 28:13.019
SO A COUPLE OF FRIENDS
AND I CHIPPED IN.

28:13.070 --> 28:15.209
DO NOT ASK ME WHO
'CAUSE I'M NOT GONNA TELL YOU.

28:15.240 --> 28:20.416
BUT I THOUGHT IT WAS STUPID
AND I'M NOT GONNA DO IT AGAIN.

28:21.350 --> 28:22.829
OKAY?

28:27.870 --> 28:31.385
SORRY FOR NOT BEING THE GIRL
THAT YOU THOUGHT I WAS.

28:33.220 --> 28:35.040
OKAY.

28:38.780 --> 28:43.149
[cell phone ringing]

28:43.200 --> 28:45.088
- HELLO.
- SARAH, HI. IT'S EDWIN CHUNG.

28:45.130 --> 28:47.018
HOW ARE YOU?
- OH, HI. I'M GOOD.

28:47.070 --> 28:49.209
HOW ARE YOU?
- GOOD. DO YOU HAVE A SECOND?

28:49.240 --> 28:51.891
- YEAH. SURE.
THAT WAS REALLY FUN TODAY.

28:51.930 --> 28:53.898
- LISTEN, I AM SO SORRY,
UNFORTUNATELY,

28:53.930 --> 28:56.171
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK OUT.

28:58.150 --> 29:00.004
- OH.
- YEAH. I THINK YOU'RE GREAT.

29:00.040 --> 29:01.314
I DO. AND I WAS FIGHTING
FOR YOU.

29:01.360 --> 29:03.385
BUT MY BOSSES JUST WON'T
HIRE ANYONE

29:03.430 --> 29:04.385
WITHOUT A COLLEGE DEGREE.

29:04.430 --> 29:07.081
IN ANY CASE,
I WANTED TO CALL YOU PERSONALLY

29:07.120 --> 29:08.769
TO LET YOU KNOW
HOW SORRY I AM.

29:08.810 --> 29:10.459
- RIGHT. SURE.

29:10.500 --> 29:11.979
- OH. AND MY BOSSES
WANTED ME

29:12.020 --> 29:13.089
TO MAKE SURE TO THANK
YOUR BROTHER,

29:13.130 --> 29:15.269
ADAM BRAVERMAN
AT T&S FOOTWEAR.

29:15.300 --> 29:18.292
- YEAH, BUT--BUT WHY DO--
DO--DO YOU KNOW HIM?

29:18.340 --> 29:19.887
- YEAH. THAT'S WHY
YOU WERE BROUGHT IN.

29:19.930 --> 29:22.615
I THOUGHT YOU KNEW.
- YEAH. YEAH.

29:22.650 --> 29:24.060
OH, YEAH. RIGHT.
OF COURSE.

29:24.100 --> 29:25.374
NO, NO. I--THAT'S--
THAT'S RIGHT.

29:25.410 --> 29:27.298
I FORGOT. I WILL.
I'LL DEFINITELY SAY HI TO HIM.

29:27.350 --> 29:30.899
THANKS. OKAY.
THANKS SO MUCH. BYE-BYE.

29:33.730 --> 29:35.869
HOW WAS SCHOOL?
- CAN WE JUST GO, PLEASE?

29:35.910 --> 29:37.593
- OH, GOD, CAN YOU JUST
NOT GIVE ME THIS ATTITUDE?

29:37.630 --> 29:38.494
NOT TODAY.

29:38.530 --> 29:39.872
- CAN YOU JUST DRIVE THE CAR,
PLEASE?

29:39.910 --> 29:40.763
- YES.
I CAN DRIVE THE CAR.

29:40.810 --> 29:42.186
I JUST WANT TO TELL YOU
AND REMIND YOU--

29:42.220 --> 29:43.426
- CAN WE PLEASE
NOT DO THIS HERE?

29:43.470 --> 29:45.188
- THAT THIS IS NOT A PUNISHMENT.
ALL YOU DO IS BE NEGATIVE.

29:45.230 --> 29:46.674
- PLEASE RESPECT MY OPINION.
- AND COMPLAIN.

29:46.710 --> 29:48.439
- I DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.
- AND GET YOUR COUSIN ARRESTED.

29:48.470 --> 29:50.529
- OH. OKAY. YEAH.
AND THAT WAS MY FAULT.

29:50.580 --> 29:51.808
- OKAY.
- IT WASN'T. I'M SERIOUS.

29:51.850 --> 29:54.501
LISTEN TO ME, PLEASE!
I DIDN'T SMOKE POT.

29:54.550 --> 29:55.858
AND I DIDN'T GIVE ANY TO HER.

29:55.890 --> 29:57.096
AND I DIDN'T ENCOURAGE HER
TO SMOKE IT.

29:57.140 --> 30:00.348
BUT YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME.
EVER. YOU DIDN'T EVEN LISTEN.

30:00.380 --> 30:01.233
AND AS FOR THIS SCHOOL,

30:01.280 --> 30:02.588
I'M REALLY GLAD
THAT YOU SENT ME HERE

30:02.620 --> 30:04.133
BECAUSE THEY'RE
HOLDING ME BACK.

30:04.180 --> 30:05.442
- WHAT?
- YEAH, I GOT HELD BACK.

30:05.490 --> 30:07.105
I'M GONNA HAVE TO DO
TENTH GRADE ALL OVER AGAIN.

30:07.150 --> 30:09.175
SO THANKS A LOT
FOR MAKING ME GO HERE.

30:09.220 --> 30:10.528
- WHAT?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

30:10.560 --> 30:12.175
- THEY'RE MAKING ME DO
TENTH GRADE OVER AGAIN

30:12.220 --> 30:14.142
BECAUSE THEY DIDN'T LIKE
MY TRANSCRIPTS FROM FRESNO.

30:14.190 --> 30:15.282
- WHO IS?
- I DON'T KNOW.

30:15.330 --> 30:16.979
I DON'T KNOW, I JUST--
- WHO SAID THAT?

30:17.020 --> 30:21.013
- I'M TAKING THE BUS.
- AMBER, COME ON.

30:25.270 --> 30:29.639
- WE'RE OUT OF HERE. HA HA HA.
- WHOOP.

30:29.680 --> 30:31.159
- WELL, MAX DID JUST GREAT.

30:31.200 --> 30:32.474
MAX, HOW ABOUT
YOU HANG OUT HERE,

30:32.520 --> 30:33.748
PLAY A LITTLE WITH THE TOYS.

30:33.790 --> 30:35.348
AND YOUR MOM AND DAD
AND I WILL GO TALK

30:35.380 --> 30:36.369
FOR A FEW MINUTES.

30:36.420 --> 30:39.378
- OKAY.
- KISSES. OKAY?

30:46.910 --> 30:50.016
- WELL?
- WELL, MAX...

30:50.050 --> 30:51.039
IS A WONDERFUL BOY.

30:51.090 --> 30:54.253
HE'S SMART. HE'S SWEET.
HE IS VERY INTELLIGENT.

30:54.300 --> 30:55.983
- OKAY, DOCTOR,
I'M SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

30:56.020 --> 30:57.635
I DON'T WANT TO BE RUDE,
BUT WE JUST WANT TO KNOW.

30:57.680 --> 31:01.127
I MEAN, DOES--DO YOU THINK
MAX HAS ASPERGER'S?

31:01.160 --> 31:02.297
- MAX IS
VERY HIGH FUNCTIONING.

31:02.340 --> 31:05.161
BUT I DO FIND
THAT MAX'S BEHAVIORS

31:05.200 --> 31:10.092
ARE CONSISTENT
WITH AN ASPERGER'S DIAGNOSIS.

31:14.800 --> 31:16.791
- OH, MY GOD.
- ALL RIGHT.

31:16.840 --> 31:18.341
UH, THIS IS FINE.

31:18.390 --> 31:20.620
WE'RE GONNA--
LOOK, WE CAN WORK THROUGH THIS.

31:20.670 --> 31:22.149
IT'S NOT AN INSURMOUNTABLE
PROBLEM.

31:22.190 --> 31:23.259
- NO.

31:23.290 --> 31:24.837
- I THINK WE SHOULD
JUST TACKLE THIS ONE-BY-ONE.

31:24.880 --> 31:26.108
SO PIRATE COSTUME.

31:26.160 --> 31:27.843
I THINK GETTING HIM OUT
OF THAT THING IS KEY.

31:27.880 --> 31:29.848
- WELL, I'M--I'M HAPPY TO HELP
WITH STRATEGIES

31:29.880 --> 31:31.507
FOR SPECIFIC BEHAVIORS.

31:31.540 --> 31:32.507
I THINK THAT WE SHOULD START

31:32.540 --> 31:34.394
WITH MORE OF
A BIG PICTURE CONVERSATION.

31:34.440 --> 31:36.328
- I'M JUST--I'M BETTER
WITH PRACTICAL STUFF.

31:36.370 --> 31:38.258
SO YOU KNOW, I JUST WANT TO--
WE GOT TO GET MOVING ON THIS.

31:38.310 --> 31:39.095
- ADAM, CAN YOU JUST--
- WHAT?

31:39.130 --> 31:41.098
- CAN YOU PLEASE
JUST LET HIM TALK?

31:41.140 --> 31:43.517
HE'S SORRY.
- NO. GO FOR IT.

31:43.550 --> 31:46.963
- THANKS.
- OKAY.

31:47.000 --> 31:49.309
THIS ISN'T A PRISON SENTENCE.
- I KNOW.

31:49.350 --> 31:50.829
- SO HOW LONG IS THIS
GOING TO TAKE THEN?

31:50.870 --> 31:53.213
- HOW LONG WILL WHAT TAKE?
- JUST TO GET HIM THROUGH THIS.

31:53.250 --> 31:54.626
GET HIM BACK ON TRACK.

31:54.670 --> 31:57.070
- OKAY, UNFORTUNATELY,
THERE IS NO CURE FOR ASPERGER'S.

31:57.120 --> 32:00.738
IT IS A SYNDROME THAT
HE WILL ALWAYS HAVE. OKAY?

32:00.780 --> 32:02.498
- I-I DON'T--
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

32:02.540 --> 32:04.940
- SORRY. WHAT--WHAT ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO FOR HIM?

32:04.990 --> 32:06.127
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW--

32:06.160 --> 32:09.846
- YOU WILL HELP TO UNCOVER
MAX'S GIFTS.

